@keyframes rule controls what happens during that animation
properties control how the animation should behave 

animation-duration sets the length of time for the animation

button:hover {
    animation-name: background-color;
    animation-duration: 500ms;
  }
  @keyframes background-color {
    100% {
      background-color: #4791d0;
    }
  }
  
  
  animation-fill-mode: forwards; the button wont revert back to the original color. button will stay highlighted.


animation-iteration-count run continuously by setting that value to infinite

@keyframes rules or animation-duration to change the rate of animation

animation-timing-function controls how quickly an animated element changes over the duration
